| ShortSummary=To raise the school's grade point average as part of the No Child Left Behind  program, Bobby and Joseph are put into a "special needs" class, which irks Hank, who believes his son's mediocre grades are from lack of trying. And things get worse when Principal Moss lets the "special needs" kids go on a trip to Alamo Land on the same day as the honors students.
| LineColor=CBA135
}}
